The paper discusses the use of Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs) for modeling student learning, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of neural networks for intelligent curriculum design, which falls under natural language processing (NLP) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper discusses the challenges and benefits of knowledge tracing in computer-supported education, which could be relevant to the sub-categories of cybernetics (cs.CY) and education technology (cs.EDU).
